snippet.textDisplay:
In the words of 'mang4':
"… We basically paid an unfinished game full price…
+ pay more to just add the content who should have been in first place (dlc)…
+ pay more for system who is limited by the fact pokemons are prisoners (home)…
+ more dlc later for the same games…

Basically, we paid 100$ for the same game with half baked animations, silly banned concept, forced additional content who was available for "free" since 2003 (previous dex)…

Do you understand at this point, GF literally sells old pokemons piece by piece? And they lied to us all along with their theory of capacity, or else? If they add dlc with previous pokemon, the models are already present… They can't add previous pokemon on an already released game if they aren't encrypted inside. And they again reuse 3ds models… When i check YouTube about this dlc, i see 10 videos about the fact it's great… Are they all stupid or blind? They literally support the fact to buy 2x the same thing, full price. You don't have "more content", you have just the content who should have been included in first place, was already inside, but was deleted to sell it one more time after the holydays and first wave of buyers…

Seriously, nobody see the problem, or is everybody so full of "i don't care take my money" spirit they just erase all the truth and accept everything stamped pokemon? I say that and i'm basically a guy who bought every gen main game since 1998... Even before the national dex retro compatibility…

"gotta catch'em all..."
"gotta buy'em all" is more accurate."
